00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:14.000
 Churchill, Manitoba, the polar bear capital of the world 

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:38.000
 When you see polar bears sitting on the shores of Hudson Bay, you feel awe. 

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:42.000
 They feel the impact of climate change. 

00:00:42.500 --> 00:00:48.000
 As temperatures increase in the world, we are seeing a decline in sea ice. 

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:51.000
 Polar bears rely on sea ice to survive. 

00:00:52.500 --> 00:00:54.000
 The bear uses sea ice to reach its main source of food 

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:56.000
 In some cases, bears are used to build their holes. 

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:04.000
 At the International Polar Preservation Organization, our mission is to rescue polar bears by saving their habitat from sea ice. 

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:12.000
 The International Polar Preservation Organization has its headquarters here in Churchill 

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:15.000
 We are in town for public education of citizens 

00:01:15.330 --> 00:01:19.500
 But most of our work is abroad in Tundra. 

