 Once you get close to the polar bear and look at it, holding your breath is an amazing moment. 

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:29.000
 One of the unique things you experience while trying to preserve the polar bear habitat 

00:02:29.330 --> 00:02:34.000
 That in many other species you can only build a fence around her home and warn people "forbidden entry here and forbidden to cut." 

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:36.000
 Polar bears live on sea ice. 

00:02:36.330 --> 00:02:40.000
 If a fence is built around the ice, it does not matter, you will not save the ice fence, 

00:02:40.200 --> 00:02:45.000
 But people in the south can reduce carbon emissions and reduce their presence on the sea ice 

00:02:45.330 --> 00:02:48.000
 This in turn will help save the sea ice. 

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:54.000
 So bringing all of this together visually to be explored by people themselves may be the solution 

00:02:55.000 --> 00:03:00.000
 I think Google Maps and Virtual Tour allow people to roam freely here 

00:03:00.500 --> 00:03:03.500
 As if they were already here 

